t is incompatible with being partisan. Over time I came to what is perhaps =
a more sophisticated understanding, which is that elections are not based o=
n voters=E2=80=99 views but that views are determined by the massive histor=
ical forces that shape human thought and generate those opinions. Since dif=
ferent people experience those forces in different ways, we wind up with di=
fferent people having different views of the same thing. If you can underst=
and the impersonal forces of economics, geopolitics and the rest, you can u=
nderstand and to some extent predict the options that are open, and underst=
and the way that opinions are shaped and divided between nations, within na=
tions and between people.&nbsp;<br>
&nbsp;<br>
