, but that the citizens are and should be divided. Tyrannies emerge from so=
cieties where there is an overwhelming consensus that crushes diversity. A =
healthy democracy avoids tyranny partly because of a divided population and=
 the constant evolution of belief. So read by one citizen, my article seems=
 to be based on admiration for the president, the other sees it based on lo=
athing.&nbsp; It is this division that guarantees a democratic society.&nbs=
p;<br>
&nbsp;<br>
