ts. Sentiment surrounding Lyndon Johnson Richard Nixon was no less divided =
or intense than the sentiment surrounding Trump.&nbsp; When we accuse Trump=
 of wanting to be a dictator, we are levelling an accusation that many pres=
idents since the founding have faced. From my point of view, Trump has twic=
e been elected by the majority of voters. He, more than most candidates, di=
d not make an attempt to hide his personality or his core beliefs. He was e=
lected, and the people have spoken. For me, the social and economic forces =
of America and the world caused his election.&nbsp; His majority is kept in=
 check by the vigorous loathing of him and the deep belief by many that his=
 presidency is dangerous and in some way illegitimate. That powerful sense =
shapes and defines his presidency and reflects a deep division that has dev=
